      "sha256": "65101d5326eb98b5b1579f1c02d266caf52734caf0cb2447683b98d555a190ff",
      "source_region": "div.problem-additional-text",
      "text": "This is a stronger form of the Erd\\H{o}s-Tur\\'{a}n conjecture [28] (since establishing this for any function $g(N)\\to \\infty$ would imply a positive solution to [28])."
    },
    "statement": {
      "sha256": "aacff663992d21de453fe79d99ebfcf35f337f9676065984be8582602e23ae70",
      "source_region": "div#content",
      "text": "For what functions $g(N)\\to \\infty$ is it true that\\[\\lvert A\\cap \\{1,\\ldots,N\\}\\rvert \\gg \\frac{N^{1/2}}{g(N)}\\]implies $\\limsup 1_A\\ast 1_A(n)=\\infty$?"
    }
  },
